latestPosts.caption:
- Who's one of your biggest inspirations? 
“A pani puri vendor in Mumbai. He’s the founder, the finance guy, the chef, and the customer care team all rolled into one.”

Meet Tarun Sharma, Co-founder and CEO of Pep Brands, house of @mcaffeineofficial and @letshyphen. His story is a masterclass in hustle, humility, and homegrown innovation.

They started with coffee-based body scrubs in mCaffeine to now a more holistic, diversified brand in bodycare segment. They have also built a skincare brand Hyphen that feels like your cool, no-nonsense dermatologist. Tarun is reshaping the beauty space, building for India and taking it to the world.

His team may be made up of first-timers, but they’ve built something that’s far from amateur. Like he says, “We’re a special aam team.”

This is the latest edition of Creators: In this series, we're featuring founders that have grown a mere idea into something grand. Stay tuned for more.

latestPosts.caption:
We at Pep Brands ( mCaffeine  and HYPHEN ) had debated on the culture of the company for many years. As we moved forward in our 10 year journey of running the company, it became increasingly clear that whatever the culture tangent we decide on, we need to make sure it’s actionable. During this process, we made a lot of mistakes. Tons of them. Some of the mistakes were near fatal as well. 

For the last couple of years, we solidified the entire set of learnings on culture. We would want to be a SPORTS TEAM rather than a FAMILY. At the core, the characteristics of a Sports team is what resonates more with us than a Family.

— The teams gets together for the “love of the game” rather than a common “last name”. 
— Extremely performance driven and very methodological in selection and placement of members 
— Only Talent doesn’t give you the right to continue to play. 
— No matter how talented you are, you will have to train like it’s your first day. 
— No hierarchy on the ground. 
— Players come and go, game remains supreme. 

There are many more characteristics which we live by every day. At the core, it is the mindset of a sports player that is making us do what we think we are capable of doing. We have seen dramatic results in the last 2 years of company life. We believe, as the game gets bigger, we will have to deepen our core as a sports team.

latestPosts.caption:
In my 15 years of start up journey, I have been fortunate to have a lot of operators around me. I have always enjoyed my conversations with them. The most fascinating part for me is that each operator brings an incredibly unique skill set in the conversation. 

And then I met Mr KRS Jamwal ❤️

My interactions with him has been “expedited MBA” in business building, risk mitigation, governance, customer closeness and so many more topics. 2 years ago, I was extremely confused in my head. I came to meet Jamwal sir and may be he sensed my inner conflict. I had a 60 mins scheduled with him. He gave me 120. Asked about my parents, about my health, told me stories about his upbringing and slowly he brought me to conflict resolution and gave me so many learnings which became the rockbed of our transformation. Amongst the many was - “Default Alive”. He very sweetly said - Just be “Default alive” tarun. I know you can do it. Something flipped in my mind suddenly. May be the confidence sir had, may be knowing that there are such fantastic people supporting me, or may be something else - But something flipped 

Me and Vaishali make sure that we meet sir every quarter. Last quarter we met him and learned a new set of things on new technologies. That has made both of us fairly productive in the last 3 months. Super blessed to have him around us and mentoring us 🙏

latestPosts.caption:
I have always kept on thinking on how my values in life would have shaped up - Was it my first 15 years of schooling, my Kota stint, ISM journey or last 15 years of start up journey. While each and every piece of the life stage had its own impact- one thing which was a constant was my mother. She is an absolute powerhouse. Extremely ambitious. Humble to the core. Very hard working. Very fundamental first. No non sense. Deep rooted belief that the fair/good behaviour travel the farthest. Honest and much more ❤️🙏🙏

Last month she retired from her job being a teacher for  36 years. In her farewell, I saw students lining up to share the work of the event. These students studied from her, 10-12 years back but still had the love and respect. Her current students were asking for her number to stay in touch for guidance. These kids did her farewell of almost 500 people, flawlessly. I had goosebumps multiple times during that day 🥹🥹

Everyday, I wish if I can have only 1% of her qualities, I would consider me lucky and successful. 

The other super woman I have been lucky with is Vaishali. Last 1 year of seeing her motherhood has made me a significantly better human being. Looking at her taking care of Ved ( amidst the roller coaster the business has been in the last 1 year ) is heartwarming and have made me believe - Maa to Maa hi hoti hai ❤️❤️. Ved “Maa ke kandhon” pe ghumega ❤️

I sleep with only 1 thought - I am blessed to have these 2 around me. That’s the most peaceful sleep I get.

latestPosts.caption:
End of the Q4 called for a toast to the Performers of the Quarter!!!!! 🎖️

11 brilliant brilliant individuals 
11 rockstars
but most importantly, 11 inspirations of the entire PEP family!

The evening was filled with discussing key milestones, their incredible efforts and obviously a lot of laughter ☺️

With our 5H’s philosophy: Hunger, Hustle, Honesty, Humility, and Humor which defines who we are. And this quarter, these 11 performers embodied it brilliantly, making a real impact 🥳🤩

But at PEP brands, we believe appreciation shouldn’t be a fleeting moment—it should be framed. Quite literally!!!!

So we inaugurated the “Wall of Fame”—a space that celebrates our STAR performers of the quarter and it talks only INSPIRATION. 

This wall is a daily boost of positive energy, a reminder that your efforts mean so much to everyone at Pep and they never go unnoticed. 

Wall of Fame completely changes the whole vibe of the PEP office—fueling ambition, spreading smiles, and keeping the caffeine (and inspiration) flowing. 

Safe to say, it’s our new favorite spot!!!

latestPosts.caption:
Work shouldn’t feel like a battle on your not-so-great days ❌

Women go through different phases in their lives—physically and mentally—which take time to adjust to and get comfortable with. It could be your first day of periods, a low morning, a sleepless night with your child, or just a normal, random, confusing day!

We understand the need for space—to take a break, breathe for a moment, and return with renewed energy.

So, we did something… 🤠

We introduced the De-Caff Comfort & NO-JUDGEMENT Room—a space exclusively for our women to rest, recharge, or simply take a break from the many things life throws at them. With recliners, hot bags, chocolates, books, and cozy couches, we aimed to bring the feeling of home into the workplace. A place where they can GO & CHILL, without being judged. 🤓

At Pep Brands, every day is about creating a workplace where women feel valued, cared for, and understood 🫂.

To all the powerful women at Pep—this one’s for you! ❤️

And yes—Happy Women’s Day, every day!
